  "dataCollection": "JAS-2v2 was constructed from professional sports broadcasts and publicly accessible online match footage. Rallies were segmented into temporally ordered action units and annotated with action category, acting-player position, and sequence-level score outcome. The public release focuses on structured annotations, split definitions, and metadata rather than redistribution of raw source videos.",
  "dataBiases": "The dataset covers four representative 2v2 sports but does not span all tactical settings or camera conditions. Most samples are derived from professional-level broadcasts with relatively consistent viewpoints, which may underrepresent amateur play, alternative viewing angles, and noisier match footage. Action-category frequencies may also vary across sports and classes.",
  "personalSensitiveInformation": "The dataset is derived from publicly broadcast sports footage and the public release contains annotations and metadata rather than raw source videos. No private personal information is intentionally collected as part of the released benchmark package."
}
